cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the task of 3D pose estimation from 2D images, which is a core problem in computer vision. The paper also introduces a new large-scale dataset for fine-grained object categories, which is relevant to the computer vision community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for segmentation, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves manual annotation and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and comparisons, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
